<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id27fad227-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419" identifier="/us/usc/t45/s1345"><num value="1345">§ 1345.</num><heading> Effect on contracts</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this subchapter shall affect any obligation of the Corporation to carry out its transportation contracts and equipment leases, equipment trusts, and conditional sales agreements, in accordance with their terms.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id27fad228-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419">(<ref href="/us/pl/99/509/tIV/s4037">Pub. L. 99–509, title IV, § 4037</ref>, <date date="1986-10-21">Oct. 21, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/1909">100 Stat. 1909</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
